commitResults.messageTitle: Configure build.gradle for compilation "./gradlew run" can now be used to build and run the project.
implement Level 1: Greet, Echo, Exit Greets the user, echos commands entered, and exits when "bye" is entered as the command. Horizontal header line and indents are printed.
Implement Level 2: Add, List Any number of tasks can be added. Tasks can be listed with the command "list".
Implement Level 3: Mark as Done Tasks can now be marked as done with the "done [task number]" command. Some input validation and error handling is done for the "done" command.
Implement Level 4: ToDos, Events, Deadlines Tasks can now be added with the "todo", "event" and "deadline" commands.
Implement Text UI Testing The text UI can be tested with the shell command "sh text-ui-text/runtest.sh" (from the project directory).
Implement Level 5: Handle Errors Text UI now handles malformed user input. Exceptions are thrown upon encountering malformed input, and caught by the main command loop.
Implement Level 6: Delete Tasks can now be deleted from the list of tasks with the "delete" command.
Implement Level 7: Save Task data is now saved to disk on exit and is restored on startup. An initial prompt is shown to the user if the task data file does not exist.

Implement Level 8: Dates and Times Dates (such as in the "deadline" and "event" commands) are now parsed and stored as LocalDate objects instead of String objects. Dates are inputted in "yyyy-mm-dd" format and outputed in "MMM d yyyy" format.

Refactor to use more OOP Program logic is now split into Ui, Storage, Parser and TaskList as required in the A-MoreOOP increment. Additionally, commands are split into their respective *Command classes.
Add JUnit tests Minimal JUnit tests have been added for TaskList.java and Parser.java. In particular, the tests for TaskList.java satisfy the minimum requirements of having more than 2 test methods.

Fix double "Error" header in error message Duke no longer prints the error message for failing to load the task data file as "Error: Error: Failed to load task list", instead correctly omitting the first "Error: "
Configure build.gradle for jarfile generation Jarfiles of Duke can now be generated with "./gradlew shadowJar" shell command
Add JavaDoc comments
Implement Level 9: Find The "find" command now displays tasks whose description matches the query string.

Adhere minimally to coding style Due to time constraints, a relaxed version of the CS2030 coding style ( https://nus-cs2030.github.io/1718-s2/style/index.html ) is adopted. Lines are at most 100 characters long, there are 4 spaces per indent, and methods are separated by at least one newline.
Conform to sample Gradle checkstyle configuration Many checkstyle and linting errors have been fixed. All JavaDoc comments now also conform to CS2103T present tense and punctuation rules.
Rename variables to conform to coding style

Refactor UI component as an interface `Ui` is now an interface, and the `Cli` class implements command-line functionality. This should assist a future implementation of a GUI (by implementing a `Gui` class).

Add initial working GUI for Level 10 A JavaFX window now opens with the "./gradlew run" shell command. This window is the newly implemented GUI for Duke. The current GUI is very basic, displaying only text output without further formatting, and does not display entered user input.
Remove unneeded comments from code

Implement task sorting: C-Sort Tasks can now be sorted with the "sort" command. Tasks with dates (e.g. Deadline, Event) will be sorted in ascending order of date and placed before tasks without dates (e.g. Todo). Tasks without dates will retain their relative ordering between each other.
Implement help comamnd: C-Help Help for commands can now be displayed with the "help [command name]" command.

Refactor code: A-CodeQuality This commit introduced general code quality changes: _ Moved code into packages _ Removed no-argument empty constructors as they are unneeded and will be automatically generated anyway. _ Moved @SuppressWarnings closer to local scope. _ Renamed all instances 'Todo' to 'ToDo' to conform to camel case.
Add assertions: A-Assertions Java assertions (i.e. "assert" keyword) have been added to various parts of the code. They denote preconditions necessary for Duke to function correctly.
